      "source": [
        "### Using the Best Model for Prediction\n",
        "\n",
        "We'll use the Logistic Regression model, which had the highest accuracy, to predict the sentiment of new text. This involves applying the same preprocessing and TF-IDF vectorization steps to the new input text."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "5a0a14a2",
        "outputId": "3b474339-4f58-4669-969e-0c316ed1206a"
      },
      "source": [
        "def predict_sentiment(text, model, vectorizer, lemmatizer, stop_words):\n",
        "    # Apply the same preprocessing steps as training data\n",
        "    processed_text = preprocess_text(text) # Re-using the preprocess_text function defined earlier\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Vectorize the preprocessed text\n",
        "    text_tfidf = vectorizer.transform([processed_text])\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Make prediction\n",
        "    prediction = model.predict(text_tfidf)\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Return sentiment label\n",
        "    return 'positive' if prediction[0] == 1 else 'negative'\n",
        "\n",
        "# Example usage with a new review\n",
        "new_review1 = \"This movie was absolutely fantastic! I loved every moment of it. Highly recommend.\"\n",
        "new_review2 = \"Terrible film, a complete waste of time. The acting was awful and the plot made no sense.\"\n",
        "new_review3 = \"It was okay, not great, not bad. Just very average.\"\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"Review 1: '{new_review1}' -> Predicted Sentiment: {predict_sentiment(new_review1, log_reg_model, tfidf_vectorizer, lemmatizer, stop_words)}\")\n",
        "print(f\"Review 2: '{new_review2}' -> Predicted Sentiment: {predict_sentiment(new_review2, log_reg_model, tfidf_vectorizer, lemmatizer, stop_words)}\")\n",
        "print(f\"Review 3: '{new_review3}' -> Predicted Sentiment: {predict_sentiment(new_review3, log_reg_model, tfidf_vectorizer, lemmatizer, stop_words)}\")"
      ],
      "execution_count": 35,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "Review 1: 'This movie was absolutely fantastic! I loved every moment of it. Highly recommend.' -> Predicted Sentiment: positive\n",
            "Review 2: 'Terrible film, a complete waste of time. The acting was awful and the plot made no sense.' -> Predicted Sentiment: negative\n",
            "Review 3: 'It was okay, not great, not bad. Just very average.' -> Predicted Sentiment: negative\n"
          ]
        }
      ]
